{
  "$comment": [
    "Tier-2 DB-state fixture spec for the `chat_settings` repo (Phase-2), a plain",
    "main-DB AbstractBaseRepository with the WIDEST JSON-object surface yet (~33",
    "columns, ~15 nested typed-struct JSON columns). One committed file drives BOTH",
    "sides of the differential:",
    "  - the v4 oracle (build-chat-settings-fixture.ts + chat-settings-tier2.ts) and",
    "  - the Rust port (quilltap-harness chat_settings tier-2 test).",
    "",
    "What this repo banks: two UUID TEXT (id, userId); one enum TEXT",
    "(avatarDisplayMode) + one plain-string TEXT (avatarDisplayStyle); a record/map",
    "JSON column (tagStyles, kept {} — multi-key open-JSON key-order seam); ~15",
    "nested typed-struct JSON-object columns reproduced in schema field order;",
    "five nullable UUID/string TEXT columns (imageDescriptionProfileId,",
    "uncensoredImageDescriptionProfileId, defaultRoleplayTemplateId, timezone, plus",
    "nested *ProfileId); five boolean columns (autoDetectRng, compositionModeDefault,",
    "composerSpellcheck, textReplacementsEnabled, autoScrollOnResponseComplete); and",
    "the FIRST INTEGER-affinity number column (sidebarWidth: z.number().min(256)",
    ".max(512) — both bounds integer, so mapToSQLiteType assigns INTEGER, unlike the",
    "prior min-only/bare REAL number columns).",
    "",
    "KEY-ORDER DISCIPLINE: v4's _create runs validate() (Zod .parse), which re-emits",
    "object keys in SCHEMA declaration order before JSON.stringify. So the stored",
    "JSON key order is fixed by the schema regardless of the input order here. The",
    "Rust typed structs declare fields in the same schema order, so to_string()",
    "matches byte-for-byte. The nested .nullable().optional() (no-default) fields",
    "the corpus OMITS (themePreference.customOverrides, timestamp customFormat/",
    "fictionalBase*, dangerous uncensored*ProfileId/customClassificationPrompt) are",
    "omitted by Zod too; the ones supplied as explicit null (cheapLLMSettings",
    "*ProfileId, storyBackgrounds defaultImageProfileId) stay present as null.",
    "",
    "OPEN-JSON KEY-ORDER DEFERRAL: tagStyles and the nested record fields",
    "(perCharacterCapOverrides) are kept {} so the serde_json::Value (sorts keys)",
    "vs JSON.stringify (insertion order) divergence never triggers. Close before",
    "data with multi-key tagStyles/overrides.",
    "",
    "SAFETY: testPepperBase64 is a THROWAWAY 32-byte key, the same one the folders/",
    "tags/connection-profiles fixtures use. NOT the real Friday pepper; safe to commit.",
    "",
    "DETERMINISM: every id and timestamp is pinned, so both sides produce",
    "byte-identical post-op state and the canonical dump needs ZERO normalization."
  ],
